The paper deals with reinforcement learning agents for question-answering over knowledge graphs, which is a common topic in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the challenges of using these agents for real-world applications, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The authors propose a new performance metric for evaluating question-answering agents, which involves optimizing for precision while also rewarding the agent for not answering a question. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses a supervised learning strategy for improving the performance of the reinforcement learning algorithm, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
